  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "We have been reaching up; now we drop down. The bottom row begins, and the move is the mirror of the top one - same idea, opposite direction. V sits below F, M sits below J. Both are index work: the finger dips, strikes, and comes home. Down and back, in one motion."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "C sits below D, and it goes to the left middle finger. Watch that one - the natural temptation is to lean the whole hand down after it. Don't. Keep the home keys anchored and let the single finger do the travelling. The rest of the hand stays put as your map."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🖐",
      "title": "Down, then straight home",
      "text": "The bottom row tempts you to leave a finger resting down there between letters. Resist it. Strike and return, every time, so the hand always knows where it is. A finger that wanders is a finger that misses - and a miss costs you more time than the reach ever saved."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "v v v v v v v v v v m m m m m m m m m m",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Index: V and M",
      "hint": "Left index drops from F to V; right index drops from J to M. Down and home."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "c",
      "baseReps": 20,
      "keys": ["c"],
      "target": "c c c c c c c c c c c c c c c c c c c c",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Middle: C",
      "hint": "Left middle finger drops from D to C, then straight back home."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "vm cv",
      "baseReps": 7,
      "keys": ["v", "m", "c"],
      "target": "vm cv vm cv vm cv vm cv vm cv vm cv vm cv",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Down and back",
      "hint": "Alternate the drops: index to V and M, middle to C. Return home each time."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Three useful letters, and now they go into words. You will see C and V turn up constantly in plain English - cover, voice, carve - so the practice here pays off in every sentence to come. Read each word whole and keep the rhythm even; the bottom row rewards a steady hand."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "A clean, even rhythm beats a fast, ragged one. The reader never sees your speed - only your mistakes.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "vivid cover mimic motive comma carve cave comic movie voice",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Words",
      "hint": "Words from the keys you know: cover, motive, carve, comic, movie, voice."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Every step typed? Then press Open Trainer below and make one clean run at the whole lesson. That run is the one that counts - it saves your progress and opens the next lesson."
    }
